quizzes.question:
Resize the background image to a height of 100 pixels and a width of 200 pixels.
[!raw!]
background-size: {0}px {1}px;

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The background-size Property[/h1]

The [b]background-size[/b] property adds new functionality to CSS that allows us to specify the size of background images, using either lengths or percentages. 

For example: [code format="css" codeId="608"]div {
   height: 150px;
   width: 200px;
   border: 1px solid #000;
   background: url("css_logo.png") no-repeat 50% 50%;
   [b]background-size: [/b]100[b]px[/b] 100[b]px[/b];
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="3008" width="100%"]
[note]The current versions of most popular browsers - including Firefox, Safari, Chrome, Internet Explorer, and Opera - now support background-size, without the need for vendor prefixes.[/note]
